<item>
            <title>[SPARK-4170] Closure problems when running Scala app that &quot;extends App&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4170</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Michael Albert noted this problem on the mailing list (&lt;a href=&quot;http://apache-spark-user-list.1001560.n3.nabble.com/BUG-when-running-as-quot-extends-App-quot-closures-don-t-capture-variables-td17675.html):&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://apache-spark-user-list.1001560.n3.nabble.com/BUG-when-running-as-quot-extends-App-quot-closures-don-t-capture-variables-td17675.html):&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;object DemoBug &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; App {
    val conf = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; SparkConf()
    val sc = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; SparkContext(conf)

    val rdd = sc.parallelize(List(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;B&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;C&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;D&quot;&lt;/span&gt;))
    val str1 = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt;

    val rslt1 = rdd.filter(x =&amp;gt; { x != &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt; }).count
    val rslt2 = rdd.filter(x =&amp;gt; { str1 != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; x != &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;A&quot;&lt;/span&gt; }).count
    
    println(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;DemoBug: rslt1 = &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + rslt1 + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot; rslt2 = &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + rslt2)
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This produces the output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;DemoBug: rslt1 = 3 rslt2 = 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If instead there is a proper &quot;main()&quot;, it works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I also this week noticed that in a program which &quot;extends App&quot;, some values were inexplicably null in a closure. When changing to use main(), it was fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I assume there is a problem with variables not being added to the closure when main() doesn&apos;t appear in the standard way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
